Partner our UAV pilots for onsite coordination work. The role will be reporting directly to the project manager for day-to-day UAV deployments for inspection purposes and will be involved in project monitoring and performance.

Trainee to be involved in:
1. Coordinate and conduct of inspection programs on site.
2. Provide direct support to Project manager for audits and closing of project.
3. Upkeep quality manuals and inspection reports.
4. Advocate safe work procedures and promote safe work philosophy

Technical Skills and Competencies Trainee will learn during SGUnited Traineeship Programme:

1. Understand the different inspection techniques available such as visual inspection, thermography inspection, laser scanning and Non-destructive testing (NDT), for different sectors.
2. How to communicate, negotiate, engage and manage client professionally.
3. Gain experience in conducting audits based on auditing standards such as ISO 9001:2005
4. Understand different quality control methodology such as the requirements of a quality management system
5. Understand the risk of different sector including sector specific regulatory safety requirements and develop risk
assessment to mitigate.
6. Knowledge on sector characteristics such as the ship and oil rig structural components and reading structural drawings

Polytechnic Diploma or Professional Qualifications

Eligibility Criteria for SGUnitedTraineeships:•Singapore Citizen or Permanent Resident; anda.Graduated or graduating in calendar year 2019 or 2020 from ITEs, polytechnics, universities, or other educational institutions (e.g. private universities and overseas institutions); orb.Graduated earlier from above institutions and completed National Service in 2019 or 2020